snippet.textDisplay: I'm biased but to me this is another example of how VAR is abused. I appreciate that the CP player may have sustained a bad injury, but it's obvious from the game that the foul was a mistimed hit by Aubameyang who arrived late on the ball not something viciously intentional. And a referee is better placed to understand this in-game rather than someone looking at a slow-motion replay over and over. I don't think those at VAR are doing a favour to themselves either with these decisions.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm biased but to me this is another example of how VAR is abused. I appreciate that the CP player may have sustained a bad injury, but it's obvious from the game that the foul was a mistimed hit by Aubameyang who arrived late on the ball not something viciously intentional. snippet.textDisplay: VAR must go, I understand it makes the game and the decisions more accurate but it is just a massive issue, removing all fun from the game. I understand that the challenge was a bad foul but as Aubameyang is one of my favorite players this decision genuinely upsets me! The Sheffield United vas West Ham game with VAR was annoying as well. Watching as a neutral I was excited with the late equalizer, but of course VAR has to ruin the fun as the ball hits the player (who I believe is called Rice) on his hand as he was running and battling it out with a player from Sheffield United. I never wether to celebrate the goal or wait until the VAR check to end our fun. I understand if they need to see the season through before making the changes but I am just losing patience. As an Arsenal fan too and how we are not seeing good results recently I just wish that the season could be restarted with Arteta as our manager!
